I can see the problem. There are multiple issues in your pom.xml that prevent MapStruct from generating EmployeeMapperImpl.

1. You never defined org.mapstruct.version
You have:

<version>${org.mapstruct.version}</version>
But your <properties> contains only:

<properties>
    <java.version>17</java.version>
</properties>
So Maven doesn't know what ${org.mapstruct.version} is.

Either define it:

<properties>
    <java.version>17</java.version>
    <org.mapstruct.version>1.5.5.Final</org.mapstruct.version>
</properties>
or simply hardcode the version.

2. You have two maven-compiler-plugin entries
Currently you have:

<plugin>
    maven-compiler-plugin
    ...
</plugin>

<plugin>
    maven-compiler-plugin
    ...
</plugin>
This is incorrect. Use only one maven-compiler-plugin.

3. The first compiler plugin only registers Lombok
It currently has:

<annotationProcessorPaths>
    <path>
        <groupId>org.projectlombok</groupId>
        <artifactId>lombok</artifactId>
    </path>
</annotationProcessorPaths>
It should also include MapStruct.

4. Spring Boot version
I also noticed:

<version>4.1.0</version>
At the time of writing, Spring Boot 4.1.0 is not a standard released version. If this is intentional and available in your environment, that's fine. Otherwise, verify the version you're using. (This is separate from the MapStruct issue.)

